Rating: 4
We make these at least once a week, sometimes with parsley and cilantro or with just parsley. Instead of following the cooking method here, I use a different one that allows them to get crispy. Bake, covered with foil, for 15 minutes at 450, then uncover, turn fries with a spatula, and bake 15 minutes more. Turn fries again, bake 15 minutes more, or until crispy on all sides. They're perfectly tender inside and they don't become inedibly blackened.

