To get crispier fries, cut them a little less than 1/2", rinse them 3 times in cold water, then soak then in cold water for 30 minutes. Pat dry and continue with rest of recipe. To avoid burning, I cover pan with parchment paper and reduced heat to 400 for 40-45 min, turning once. Sometimes I turn on broiler for last 5 minutes and crisp up the tops. Yum!

